headlines.description: The World Cup Group I qualifier between Albania and Poland was suspended after bottles were thrown on the pitch from the crowd in the second half.

headlines.description: Denmark became the second European nation to qualify for the 2022 World Cup, with two games to spare, after a 1-0 home win over Austria on Tuesday.

headlines.description: Lyndon Dykes scored a controversial goal four minutes from fulltime to hand Scotland another dramatic late victory, as they beat the Faroe Islands.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scotland snatch another late World Cup winner

headlines.description: Cristiano Ronaldo scored three times for the 10th time in Portugal colors as Fernando Santos' side racked up a big win in World Cup qualifying.

tracking.trackingName: Ronaldo scores a hat trick as Portugal cruise past Luxembourg

headlines.shortLinkText: Ronaldo nets 10th Portugal hat-trick in big win

headlines.description: Two goals from striker Dusan Vlahovic steered Serbia to a 3-1 home win over Azerbaijan in their 2022 World Cup qualifier on Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vlahovic double helps Serbia beat Azerbaijan
